# Keep line endings consistent across this WSL/Unix repo. It is built with a
# Unix toolchain (Retro68, shell scripts, rb-cli), but Windows-side editors and
# tools occasionally rewrite files with CRLF. The text=auto eol=lf rule makes
# git store and check out text as LF and normalize on the fly, so a stray CRLF
# working-tree write is never committed and never shows up as a spurious git
# diff. (A local core.autocrlf=input reinforces this on the checkin side.)
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts break outright if they ever get CRLF -- pin explicitly.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Binary assets: never normalize or diff as text.
*.png  binary
*.ico  binary
*.gif  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.bin  binary
*.hfv  binary
*.hda  binary
*.img  binary
*.iso  binary
*.dsk  binary
*.rom  binary
*.sit  binary
*.hqx  binary
